item.title: When Sparta Met Loki
item.description:
When Sparta Met Loki
We introduced Sparta and Loki the night we brought Loki home from Petsmart's adoption center in Newbury Park, Ca. First we let them sniff each other under the door for the first few hours. Then we introduced them to each other early because neither one seemed to be aggressive but just to be safe we put a fence between them to keep them from attacking each other. We let then mingle for a few more hours (with supervision). Then Stephanie and I got on opposite sides of the fence to make them feel more comfortable. Once they seemed ok with each other, we let Loki out. Nothing really happened so we didn't think it would be entertaining to show but they didn't fight, growl or even look at each other the wrong way. They just got closer and closer over time.
